&lt;p&gt;The Manager, Quality Systems &amp;amp; Operations (QSO) is responsible for leading the day-to-day operation, governance, and continuous improvement of the organization’s Quality Management System (QMS) within a regulated clinical technology environment. This role serves as the operational backbone (“engine room”) of the Quality &amp;amp; Compliance function and ensures quality processes are efficient, inspection-ready, risk-based, and aligned with the needs of a clinical trial software / technology-enabled services organization.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Manager, QSO will oversee core quality system processes including document control, SOP lifecycle management, training administration and effectiveness support, quality events and CAPA management, quality metrics and management reporting, and cross-functional process improvement initiatives. This role partners closely with Product, Engineering, Information Security, Operations, Client Services, Audits &amp;amp; Assurance (AA), and Systems &amp;amp; Regulatory Compliance (SRC) to support GxP expectations, customer requirements, and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
