&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will make an impact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Technical Trainer is responsible for delivering technical enablement training, maintaining and enhancing training content, and supporting the technical aspects of our Certification and Partner Programs. The Technical Trainer shall ensure that all client work has met or exceeded client expectations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong technical aptitude with excellent communication and facilitation skills. They are comfortable learning complex software solutions, translating technical concepts into effective training experiences, and managing multiple priorities in a dynamic, client-focused environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a flexible contract position designed to support varying business and training demands. The successful candidate must be able to adapt to changing schedules and project needs while maintaining a high standard of quality and responsiveness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accelerate your skills and career within a fast-growing company while impacting the future of healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day to day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training Delivery
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver engaging instructor-led technical and enablement training programs to customers, partners, and internal audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the overall relationship and expectations of their assigned clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt training delivery based on audience needs, skill levels, and learning objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training Content Management
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update training materials to reflect product enhancements and evolving business requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with subject matter experts to ensure training content remains accurate and relevant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of new training materials, exercises, and learning resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
